Extend the tab record with `dirty`, flip it in EDIT/SAVE, and add a named guard.

```typescript
import { setup, assign } from 'xstate';

type Tab = { id: string; content: string; dirty: boolean };

export const editor = setup({
  types: {
    context: {} as { tabs: Tab[] },
    events: {} as
      | { type: 'OPEN'; id: string }
      | { type: 'EDIT'; id: string; value: string }
      | { type: 'SAVE'; id: string }
      | { type: 'CLOSE_ALL' },
  },
  guards: {
    anyDirty: ({ context }) => context.tabs.some((t) => t.dirty),
  },
}).createMachine({
  id: 'editor',
  context: { tabs: [] },
  on: {
    OPEN: {
      actions: assign({
        tabs: ({ context, event }) => [
          ...context.tabs,
          { id: event.id, content: '', dirty: false },
        ],
      }),
    },
    EDIT: {
      actions: assign({
        tabs: ({ context, event }) =>
          context.tabs.map((t) =>
            t.id === event.id ? { ...t, content: event.value, dirty: true } : t,
          ),
      }),
    },
    SAVE: {
      actions: assign({
        tabs: ({ context, event }) =>
          context.tabs.map((t) => (t.id === event.id ? { ...t, dirty: false } : t)),
      }),
    },
    CLOSE_ALL: {
      guard: 'anyDirty',
      actions: assign({ tabs: () => [] }),
    },
  },
});
```

`assign(({ spawn }) => ...)` creates a child actor whose lifetime is tied to that context slot. Each tab's internal state (content, cursor, dirty flag) lives inside its own actor, so sibling tabs can't accidentally mutate each other's state. The parent holds only `ActorRefFrom<typeof tabLogic>` and addresses children via `sendTo`.

```typescript
import { setup, assign, fromTransition, type ActorRefFrom } from 'xstate';

const tabLogic = fromTransition(
  (state: { text: string }, event: { type: 'SET'; value: string }) =>
    event.type === 'SET' ? { text: event.value } : state,
  { text: '' },
);

type TabRef = ActorRefFrom<typeof tabLogic>;

export const editor = setup({
  types: {
    context: {} as { left: TabRef | null; right: TabRef | null },
    events: {} as { type: 'OPEN_LEFT' } | { type: 'OPEN_RIGHT' },
  },
  actors: { tabLogic },
}).createMachine({
  id: 'editor',
  context: { left: null, right: null },
  on: {
    OPEN_LEFT: {
      actions: assign({ left: ({ spawn }) => spawn('tabLogic', { id: 'left' }) }),
    },
    OPEN_RIGHT: {
      actions: assign({ right: ({ spawn }) => spawn('tabLogic', { id: 'right' }) }),
    },
  },
});
```

